The paper deals with the problem of colorizing grayscale images using deep learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of classification and feature learning, which are topics commonly found in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of class-rebalancing, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
